{"title_page": "Ralph Stewart (ice hockey)", "text_new": "{{Infobox ice hockey player\n| name= Ralph Stewart\n| image=\n| caption=\n| image_size=\n| position =[[Center (ice hockey)|Centre]]\n| shoots = Left\n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in =1\n| weight_lb = 190\n| played_for=[[Vancouver Canucks]]<br>[[New York Islanders]]\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1948|12|2}}\n| birth_place =[[Fort William, Ontario|Fort William]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| career_start = 1965\n| career_end = 1979\n}}\n'''Ralph Donald Stewart''' (born December 2, 1948) is a Canadian former professional [[ice hockey]] player who played 251 games in the [[National Hockey League]] with the [[Vancouver Canucks]] and [[New York Islanders]] between 1970 and 1978. Stewart also spent several years playing in the minor league [[Central Professional Hockey League|Central Hockey League]].\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Regular season and playoffs===\n{| border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"text-align:center; width:60em\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\"|\n! rowspan=\"100\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\"|\n! colspan=\"5\"|[[Regular season]]\n! rowspan=\"100\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\"|\n! colspan=\"5\"|[[Playoffs]]\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! [[Season (sports)|Season]]\n! Team\n! League\n! GP !! [[Goal (ice hockey)|G]] !! [[Assist (ice hockey)|A]] !! [[Point (ice hockey)|Pts]] !! [[Penalty (ice hockey)|PIM]]\n! GP !! G !! A !! Pts !! PIM\n|-\n| 1962\u201363\n| [[Fort William Canadiens]]\n| [[Thunder Bay Junior A Hockey League|TBJHL]]\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| 5 || 1 || 1 || 2 || 0\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1963\u201364\n| Fort William Canadiens\n| TBJHL\n| 20 || 4 || 5 || 9 || 6\n| 12 || 8 || 5 || 13 || 8\n|-\n| 1964\u201365\n| Fort William Canadiens\n| TBJHL\n| 24 || 13 || 18 || 31 || 38\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1965\u201366 OHA season|1965\u201366]]\n| [[Montreal Junior Canadiens]]\n| [[Ontario Hockey League|OHA]]\n| 46 || 7 || 9 || 16 || 28\n| 10 || 0 || 0 || 0 || 2\n|-\n| [[1966\u201367 OHA season|1966\u201367]]\n| Montreal Junior Canadiens\n| OHA\n| 48 || 6 || 23 || 29 || 49\n| 6 || 4 || 1 || 5 || 0\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1967\u201368 OHA season|1967\u201368]]\n| Montreal Junior Canadiens\n| OHA\n| 43 || 17 || 31 || 48 || 28\n| 11 || 5 || 4 || 9 || 8\n|-\n| [[1968\u201369 WHL season|1968\u201369]]\n| [[Vancouver Canucks (WHL)|Vancouver Canucks]]\n| [[Western Hockey League (1952\u20131974)|WHL]]\n| 6 || 0 || 1 || 1 || 0\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1968\u201369 CHL season|1968\u201369]]\n| [[Houston Apollos]]\n| [[Central Professional Hockey League|CHL]]\n| 44 || 10 || 17 || 27 || 10\n| 3 || 0 || 0 || 0 || 0\n|-\n| [[1969\u201370 CHL season|1969\u201370]]\n| [[Kansas City Blues (ice hockey)|Kansas City Blues]]\n| CHL\n| 72 || 21 || 21 || 42 || 37\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1970\u201371 NHL season|1970\u201371]]\n| [[Vancouver Canucks]]\n| [[National Hockey League|NHL]]\n| 3 || 0 || 1 || 1 || 0\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n| [[1970\u201371 AHL season|1970\u201371]]\n| [[Rochester Americans]]\n| [[American Hockey League|AHL]]\n| 66 || 27 || 16 || 43 || 14\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1971\u201372 WHL season|1971\u201372]]\n| [[Seattle Totems]]\n| WHL\n| 16 || 2 || 6 || 8 || 4\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n| [[1971\u201372 AHL season|1971\u201372]]\n| [[Tidewater Wings]]\n| AHL\n| 20 || 3 || 8 || 11 || 8\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1971\u201372 CHL season|1971\u201372]]\n| [[Fort Worth Wings]]\n| CHL\n| 38 || 21 || 36 || 57 || 23\n| 7 || 6 || 6 || 12 || 6\n|-\n| [[1972\u201373 CHL season|1972\u201373]]\n| Fort Worth Wings\n| CHL\n| 39 || 29 || 36 || 65 || 23\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1972\u201373 NHL season|1972\u201373]]\n| [[New York Islanders]]\n| NHL\n| 31 || 4 || 10 || 14 || 4\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n| [[1973\u201374 NHL season|1973\u201374]]\n| New York Islanders\n| NHL\n| 67 || 23 || 20 || 43 || 6\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1974\u201375 NHL season|1974\u201375]]\n| New York Islanders\n| NHL\n| 70 || 16 || 24 || 40 || 12\n| 13 || 3 || 3 || 6 || 2\n|-\n| [[1975\u201376 NHL season|1975\u201376]]\n| New York Islanders\n| NHL\n| 31 || 6 || 7 || 13 || 2\n| 6 || 1 || 1 || 2 || 0\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1975\u201376 CHL season|1975\u201376]]\n| [[Fort Worth Texans]]\n| CHL\n| 3 || 2 || 5 || 7 || 2\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n| [[1976\u201377 NHL season|1976\u201377]]\n| Vancouver Canucks\n| NHL\n| 34 || 6 || 8 || 14 || 4\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1976\u201377 NHL season|1976\u201377]]\n| [[Tulsa Oilers (1964\u201384)|Tulsa Oilers]]\n| CHL\n| 43 || 24 || 26 || 50 || 14\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n| [[1977\u201378 NHL season|1977\u201378]]\n| Vancouver Canucks\n| NHL\n| 16 || 2 || 3 || 5 || 0\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1977\u201378 CHL season|1977\u201378]]\n| Tulsa Oilers\n| CHL\n| 50 || 16 || 29 || 45 || 12\n| 7 || 6 || 3 || 9 || 0\n|-\n| [[1978\u201379 CHL season|1978\u201379]]\n| Fort Worth Texans\n| CHL\n| 76 || 15 || 33 || 48 || 8\n| 5 || 0 || 0 || 0 || 4\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! colspan=\"3\"|CHL totals\n! 365 !! 138 !! 203 !! 341 !! 129\n! 22 !! 12 !! 9 !! 21 !! 10\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! colspan=\"3\"|NHL totals\n! 252 !! 57 !! 73 !! 130 !! 28\n! 19 !! 4 !! 4 !! 8 !! 2\n|}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{icehockeystats}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stewart, Ralph}}\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:Canadian ice hockey centres]]\n[[