}}\n! Release date\n|-\n| ''Last Man Standing: The Complete First Season''\n| align=\"center\"|24\n| rowspan=\"2\"|May 13, 2014\n|-\n| ''Last Man Standing: The Complete Second Season''\n| align=\"center\"|18\n|-\n| ''Last Man Standing: The Complete Third Season''\n| align=\"center\"|22\n| October 28, 2014\n|-\n| ''Last Man Standing: The Complete Fourth Season''\n| align=\"center\"|22\n| October 5, 2015\n|-\n| ''Last Man Standing: The Complete Fifth Season''\n| align=\"center\"|22\n| rowspan=\"2\"|June 26, 2018\n|-\n| ''Last Man Standing: The Complete Sixth Season''\n| align=\"center\"|22\n|}\n\n==Syndication==\nOn September 3, 2015, it was announced that [[Freeform (TV channel)|ABC Family]] (now Freeform) had obtained syndication rights to the series, which began airing episodes on September 28, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.sitcomsonline.com/2015/09/abc-family-fall-2015-schedule-with-last.html|title=ABC Family Fall 2015 Schedule with Last Man Standing; Girl Meets World Tackles Asperger's Syndrome in Upcoming Episode \u2013 SitcomsOnline.com News Blog|work=sitcomsonline.com}}</ref> As of 2018, Freeform no longer airs the series. On May 15, 2015, it was announced that [[Hallmark Channel]] had obtained the rights to the sitcom, and they aired the series from January 2016 until December 31, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.sitcomsonline.com/2015/05/hallmark-channel-acquires-last-man.html|title=Hallmark Channel Acquires Last Man Standing for 2016; Sitcom Stars on Talk Shows (Week of May 18, 2015) \u2013 SitcomsOnline.com News Blog|work=sitcomsonline.com}}</ref> On September 4, 2015, the series joined the [[Country Music Television|CMT]] Network with a mini-marathon of episodes. The series also joined [[WGN America]] on April 30, 2018. <!-- The series also joined [[TBS (U.S. TV channel)|TBS]] on November 5, 2018. (comment hidden as it's unreferenced and refers to a future date)--> Currently, all eight seasons are available for streaming on [[Hulu]].\n\n==Broadcast==\n''Last Man Standing'' aired on ABC in the U.S.;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2011/05/abc-unveils-2011-12-primetime-schedule-132846/|title=ABC Primetime Schedule 2011|last=|first=|date=May 17, 2011|website=|access-date=May 27, 2017}}</ref> on [[Fox8]],\n[[Network Ten]] and [[Eleven (TV channel)|Eleven]] (previously aired on [[One (Australian TV channel)|One]]) in Australia;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2013/09/fox8-premieres-sept-oct.html|title=FOX8 premieres: Sept / Oct|first=David|last=Knox|work=TV Tonight|date=September 20, 2013|accessdate=March 5, 2014}}</ref> [[City (TV network)|City]] in Canada; and [[TV3 (New Zealand)|TV3]] in New Zealand.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv3.co.nz/Shows/LastManStanding.aspx|title=Last Man Standing \u2013 Shows \u2013 TV3|work=MediaWorks|date=September 20, 2013|accessdate=March 5, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn the United Kingdom and Ireland, it premiered on October 9, 2012 on [[Sky One]],<ref name=tvwise>{{cite web|title=Sky1 Acquires UK Rights To ABC's Comedy Series 'Last Man Standing'|url=http://www.tvwise.co.uk/2012/09/sky1-acquires-uk-rights-to-abcs-comedy-series-last-man-standing/|first=Patrick|last=Munn|work=TVWise|date=September 19, 2012|accessdate=September 19, 2012}}</ref> which aired the first three seasons before dropping it due to low ratings; the show was bought by [[E4 (TV channel)|E4]], where it premiered on March 13, 2017;<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chortle.co.uk/news/2017/03/03/26999/e4_buys_last_man_standing|title=E4 buys Last Man Standing|date=March 3, 2017|work=[[Chortle]]|accessdate=24 May 2018}}</ref> [[Channel 4]] then reran the program on Sunday mornings from July until September 2017; in 2018, [[5Star]] acquired the show for reruns and new episodes.\n\nIn [[Israel]], it airs on [[yes (Israel)|yes Comedy]].{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}\n\nIn [[the Netherlands]], it is on [[RTL 7]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tvgids.net/ |website=TV GIDS |title=TV GIDS Nederland |access-date=March 20, 2019 |language=nl }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}<!--\n<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/01/11/arts/television/last-man-standing-uses-an-experienced-stable-of-writers.html?_r=0 |title=\"'Last Man Standing' Uses an Experienced Stable of Writers\" |work=New York Times |date=January 9, 2015 |accessdate=August 3, 2015 }}</ref>\n -->\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Last Man Standing}}\n* {{Official website|https://www.fox.com/last-man-standing/}}\n* {{IMDb title|1828327|Last Man Standing}}\n* {{tv.com show|last-man-standing-2011|Last Man Standing}}\n\n{{Last Man Standing}}\n{{FOXNetwork Shows (current and upcoming)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Last Man Standing (American TV series)}}\n[[Category:2011 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2017 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:2018 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s American sitcoms]]\n[[Category:2020s American sitcoms]]\n[[Category:American Broadcasting Company original programming]]\n[[Category:American television series revived after cancellation]]\n[[Category:Conservative media in the United States]]\n[[Category:Denver in fiction]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Fox Broadcasting Company original programming]]\n[[Category:Last Man Standing]]\n[[Category:Media portrayals of the working class]]\n[[Category:Teenage pregnancy in television]]\n[[Category:Television series about marriage]]\n[[Category:Television series about sisters]]\n[[Category:Television series about suburbia]]\n[[Category:Television series by 20th Century Fox Television]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Colorado]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American television sitcom}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Last Man Standing\n| image                = Last Man Standing intertitle.jpg\n| genre                = [[Sitcom]]\n| creator              = [[Jack Burditt]]\n| developer            = \n| starring             = <!-- Per template instructions, \"cast are listed in original credit order followed by order in which new cast joined the show\". -->{{Plainlist|\n* [[Tim Allen]]\n* [[Nancy Travis]]\n* [[Alexandra Krosney]]\n* [[Molly Ephraim]]\n* [[Kaitlyn Dever]]\n* [[Christoph Sanders]]\n* [[H\u00e9ctor Elizondo]]\n* [[Amanda Fuller]]\n* Flynn Morrison\n* [[Jordan Masterson]]\n* [[Jonathan Adams (American actor)|Jonathan Adams]]\n* Molly McCook\n* [[Jet Jurgensmeyer]]\n* [[Krista Marie Yu]]\n}}\n| theme_music_composer = \n| opentheme            = \n| endtheme             = \n| composer             = [[Monte Montgomery]]<br />Carl Thiel\n| country              = United States\n| language             = English\n| num_seasons          = 8\n| num_episodes         = 171\n| list_episodes        = List of Last Man Standing episodes\n| executive_producer   = {{Plainlist|\n* Tim Allen\n* Becky Clements\n* [[Marty Adelstein]]\n* [[Shawn Levy]]\n* Richard Baker\n* Rick Messina\n* [[John Pasquin]]\n* Kevin Abbott\n* Michael Shipley\n* Matt Berry\n* [[Tim Doyle]]\n* [[Kevin Hench]]\n*[[Jack Burditt]] (season 1)\n}}\n| producer             = {{Plainlist|\n* [[John Amodeo]]\n}}\n| editor               = Pamela J. Marshall\n| cinematography       = Donald A. Morgan\n| camera               = [[Multiple-camera setup|Multi-camera]]\n| runtime              = 21 minutes\n| company              = {{Plainlist|\n* [[21 Laps Entertainment|21 Laps]]-Adelstein Productions\n* NestEgg Productions\n* Double Wide Productions (season 1)\n* Mr. Big Shot Fancy-Pants Productions (seasons 2\u20134)\n* Lyonsberry Productions (seasons 5\u20136)\n* [[20th Century Fox Television]]\n}}\n| distributor          = [[20th Television]]\n| network              = [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] (2011\u20132017) <br> [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] (2018\u2013present)\n| picture_format       = [[720p]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n| audio_format         = \n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2011|10|11}}\n| last_aired           = present\n| website              = https://www.fox.com/last-man-standing/\n| production_website   = \n}}\n\n'''''Last Man Standing''''' is an American [[sitcom]] created by [[Jack Burditt]] for [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]], later airing on [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]. The show stars [[Tim Allen]] as an executive at a sporting goods store chain headquartered in Denver, Colorado, who is a married father of three daughters and a grandfather to his eldest daughter's son. ''Last Man Standing'' is a joint production by [[21 Laps Entertainment|21 Laps]]-Adelstein Productions, NestEgg Productions, and [[20th Century Fox Television]] and syndicated by [[20th Television]].\n\nThe series originally ran on ABC from 2011 to 2017 for six seasons, and entered [[broadcast syndication|syndication]] in 2015. Despite being ABC's second-highest rated sitcom for the 2016\u201317 season, it was revealed in May 2017 that the network had declined to renew ''Last Man Standing'' for a seventh season. Media publications reported that ABC was unwilling to cover the production costs for a seventh season on behalf of 20th Century Fox Television. One year later, Fox announced it had picked up the show for a seventh season, which premiered on September 28, 2018.<ref name=\"7thpremiere\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/fox-fall-premiere-dates-2018-empire-9-1-1-lethal-weapon-last-man-standing-nfl-1202418890/|title=Fox Sets Fall Premiere Dates: 'Empire', '9-1-1', Recast 'Lethal Weapon' & More|last=Pedersen|first=Erik|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=June 28, 2018|accessdate=June 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn April 18, 2019, Fox renewed the series for an eighth season,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2019/04/18/last-man-standing-renewed-season-8-fox/|title=Last Man Standing Renewed at Fox|last=Schwartz|first=Ryan|website=[[TVLine]]|date=April 18, 2019|accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref> which premiered on January 2, 2020.<ref name=\"8thpremiere\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/10/fox-midseason-premiere-dates-last-man-standing-duncanville-deputy-masked-singer-outmatched-9-1-1-lone-star-1202768301/|title=Fox Midseason Premiere Dates: 'Last Man Standing', 'Flirty Dancing', 'Deputy', 'Duncanville' & More|last=Pedersen|first=Nellie Andreeva,Erik|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|date=2019-10-24|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-10-25|last3=Pedersen|first3=Erik}}</ref>\n\n==Premise==\nThe series follows Mike Baxter, a senior executive and director of marketing for an outdoor sporting goods store chain based in [[Denver, Colorado]]. His home life is initially filled with his wife, three daughters, and a grandson, but later extends to the young men who are married to or dating his daughters.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{main|List of Last Man Standing characters}}\n\n===Main===\n* [[Tim Allen]] as Michael Martin \"Mike\" Baxter: Mike is a father of three daughters and the director of marketing for the Outdoor Man chain of sporting goods stores. Mike stanchly supports traditional, conservative values.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=[[American Radio Relay League]] |url=http://www.arrl.org/news/em-ham-radio-in-hollywood-em-comedian-tim-allen-stars-as-radio-amateur-on-new-tv-show |title=Ham Radio in Hollywood: Comedian Tim Allen Stars as Radio Amateur on New TV Show |date=December 12, 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Nancy Travis]] as Vanessa Baxter (n\u00e9e Davidson), Mike's wife: Vanessa is a [[Geology|geologist]] working in the energy industry. In season four, Vanessa becomes frustrated with her job and decides to become a high-school science teacher. After being laid off as a teacher due to budget cuts, Vanessa begins her own tutoring business.\n* [[Alexandra Krosney]] (season 1) and [[Amanda Fuller]] (seasons 2\u2013present<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2018/07/02/last-man-standing-molly-ephraim-season-7-mandy-recast/|title=Last Man Standing Shake-Up: 2 Major Roles Being Recast Ahead of Season 7|first=Michael|last=Ausiello|date=July 2, 2018|publisher=}}</ref>) as Kristin Beth Baxter, the oldest daughter, initially a teenage mother trying to raise her son on her own.\n* [[Molly Ephraim]] (seasons 1\u20136) and [[Molly McCook]] (season 7\u2013present)<ref name=recast /> as Amanda Elaine \"Mandy\" Baxter-Anderson, the fashion-focused middle daughter, who has no clue on how the real world works.\n* [[Kaitlyn Dever]] (regular, seasons 1\u20136; recurring, season 7\u2013present) as Eve Baxter, the youngest daughter, a strong scholar and athlete with military aspirations, and allegedly Mike's favorite child.<ref>{{cite web |title=Last Man Standing EP Laments That 'Unfortunate' Cast Departure |url=https://tvline.com/2018/08/02/molly-ephraim-leaving-last-man-standing-season-7-mandy-recast/ |website=TV Line |publisher=TV Line |accessdate=2 August 2018|date=August 2, 2018 }}</ref>\n* [[Christoph Sanders]] as Kyle Anderson, a young employee at Outdoor Man and later Mandy's husband.\n* [[H\u00e9ctor Elizondo]] as Edward \"Ed\" Alzate, Mike's longtime business partner, of [[Basque people|Basque]] heritage.<ref>{{cite episode|title=Rediscover America|series=Last Man Standing|credits=Vince Calandra (writer) & [[Victor Gonzalez (director)|Victor Gonzalez]] (director)|network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]|airdate=October 10, 2014|season=4|number=3}}</ref>\n* Flynn Morrison (regular, seasons 2\u20136), [[Jet Jurgensmeyer]] (regular, season 7; recurring, season 8)<ref name=recast /> and Evan and Luke Kruntchev (recurring, season 1) as Boyd Baxter, son of Kristin and Ryan and grandson of Mike and Vanessa.\n* [[Jordan Masterson]] (regular, seasons 4\u2013present; recurring, seasons 2\u20133) and [[Nick Jonas]] (guest star, season 1) as Ryan Vogelson, Boyd's deadbeat Canadian father who later re-enters his son's life and marries Kristin. He is very \"Left-wing\" in his views.\n* [[Jonathan Adams (American actor)|Jonathan Adams]] as Charles Marian \"Chuck\" Larabee (regular, seasons 4\u2013present; recurring, seasons 2\u20133): Mike and Vanessa's neighbor, a retired U.S. Marine who later becomes the head of security at Outdoor Man.\n* [[Krista Marie Yu]] as Jen (season 7\u2013present), Vanessa's foreign-exchange student from Hong Kong who moves in with the Baxters in season 7.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/last-man-standing-krista-yu-promoted-series-regular-fox-tim-allen-1202537375/|title='Last Man Standing': Krista Marie Yu Promoted To Regular On Fox Series|magazine=Deadline|author=Denise Petski|date=January 18, 2019|accessdate=February 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Recurring===\n* [[Kenton Duty]] as Victor Blake (season 1), Eve's soccer teammate and brief \"boyfriend\".\n* [[Robert Forster]] as Bud Baxter (seasons 1, 3\u20134, 7), Mike's widower father.\n* [[Erika Alexander]] (seasons 2\u20136) and [[Tisha Campbell-Martin|Tisha Campbell]] (season 7\u2013present) as Carol Larabee, Chuck's wife and Mike and Vanessa's neighbor.\n* [[Carla Jimenez]] as Blanca Alvarez (seasons 2\u20134), the Baxters' Guatemalan-born housekeeper who also helps Mandy with her fashion business.\n* [[Sarah Gilman]] as Cammy Harris (seasons 2\u20136), Eve's soccer teammate and extremely chatty best friend.\n* [[Jonathan Taylor Thomas]] as John Baker (seasons 2\u20133), Kristin's boss at a fancy restaurant where she works.\n* [[Tye Sheridan]] as Justin (seasons 3\u20134), Eve's fellow Jr. ROTC member, football teammate and brief boyfriend.\n* [[Zachary Gordon]] as Andrew (season 3), Eve's nerdy classmate.\n* [[Joely Fisher]] as Wendi Gracin (seasons 3\u20135), Ed's obnoxious younger girlfriend, whom he meets near the end of season three.\n* [[Bill Engvall]] as Reverend Paul (seasons 5\u2013present), the new pastor of the Baxter family's church.\n* [[Jay Leno]] as Joe Leonard (seasons 5\u2013present), a semi-retired auto technician who later works in the repair shop at Outdoor Man.\n* [[Travis Tope]] as Rob (season 6), Eve's boyfriend who is studying criminal justice at [[UC Boulder]].\n* [[Susan Sullivan]] as Bonnie Davidson (now Alzate) (seasons 7\u2013present), Vanessa's mother who becomes Ed's wife.\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Main|List of Last Man Standing episodes}}\n{{:List of Last Man Standing episodes}}\n<!-- To edit the table in this section, you need to edit the \"Series overview\" table in [[List of Last Man Standing episodes]] -->\n\n==Production==\n\n===Development and casting===\n''Last Man Standing'' first appeared on ABC's development slate in late 2010 when writer [[Jack Burditt]] received a [[put pilot]] commitment from the network under the original title ''Man Up''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deadline.com/2010/11/abc-lands-man-up-comedy-from-writer-jack-burditt-which-may-star-tim-allen/|title=ABC Lands 'Man Up' Comedy From Writer Jack Burditt Which May Star Tim Allen|date=November 8, 2010|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=August 13, 2011}}</ref> In January 2011, ABC [[green-light]]ed production of a [[Television pilot|pilot]] episode under the title ''Last Days of Man''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2011/01/19/development-update-wednesday-january-19-732524/9075/|title=Development Update: Wednesday, January 19|date=January 19, 2011|work=The Futon Critic|accessdate=August 13, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.variety.com/article/VR1118030551?refCatId=14 |title=NBC orders Ron Moore pilot |date=January 19, 2011 |last=Littleton |first=Cynthia |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/60uYZF9kC?url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1118030551?refCatId=14 |archivedate=August 13, 2011 |accessdate=August 13, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> On February 18, [[Tim Allen]], who had been attached to the potential series from the beginning, officially joined the project in the lead role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2011/02/tim-allen-returns-to-abc-roots-with-comedy-pilot|date=February 18, 2011|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|title=Home Improvement Redux: Tim Allen Returns to ABC Roots With Comedy Pilot|work=[[TVLine]]|accessdate=August 13, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deadline.com/2011/02/tim-allen-commits-to-abc-comedy-pilot|date=February 18, 2011|title=Tim Allen Commits To ABC Comedy Pilot|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=August 13, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aoltv.com/2011/02/18/tim-allen-abc-sitcom-pilot|date=February 18, 2011|title=Tim Allen Nabs ABC Sitcom Pilot|last=Harnick|first=Chris|work=AolTV|accessdate=August 13, 2011}}</ref> At the end of March, [[Nancy Travis]] joined the cast in the leading female role as Allen's \"smart and loving wife who doesn't miss much\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2011/03/29/nancy-travis-lands-lead-in-tim-allens-pilot/|title=Nancy Travis lands lead in Tim Allen's ABC pilot|date=March 29, 2011|last=Hibberd|first=James|work=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=October 1, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deadline.com/2011/03/nancy-travis-gets-female-lead-in-abcs-tim-allen-pilot-jere-burns-joins-nbc-comedy|title=Nancy Travis Gets Female Lead In ABC's Tim Allen Pilot, Jere Burns Joins NBC Comedy|date=March 29, 2011|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=August 13, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/ustv/news/a311867/nancy-travis-joins-abc-tim-allen-pilot.html|title=Nancy Travis joins ABC Tim Allen pilot|date=March 30, 2011|last=Jeffrey|first=Morgan|work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=August 13, 2011}}</ref> Soon thereafter, [[H\u00e9ctor Elizondo]] came on board in a supporting role as the boss to Allen's character.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2011/03/30/hector-elizondo-joins-tim-allen-project/|title=Hector Elizondo joins Tim Allen project|date=August 30, 2011|last=Rice|first=Lynette|work=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=October 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nOn May 13, 2011, ABC picked up the pilot for the [[2011\u201312 United States network television schedule|2011\u20132012 television season]] under the new title ''Last Man Standing''.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://ew.com/article/2011/05/13/abc-picks-up-tim-allen-comedy/|title=Tim Allen ABC comedy|date=May 13, 2011|last=Rice|first=Lynette|last2=Hibberd|first2=James|work=Entertainment Weekly|access-date=August 13, 2011}}</ref> On May 17, 2011, ABC announced that the series would air on Tuesday nights at 8 Eastern/7 Central.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2011/05/17/abc-2011-12-primetime-schedule-announced/92903|title=ABC 2011\u201312 Primetime Schedule Announced|date=May 17, 2011|last=Seidman|first=Robert|work=TV by the Numbers|access-date=August 2, 2011}}</ref> It debuted on October 11, 2011, with the first two episodes airing in a one-hour premiere.<ref name=abcpremieres>{{cite web|last=Seidman|first=Robert|title=ABC Announces Fall Series Premiere Dates: Late Starts for 'Once Upon a Time,' 'Man Up'|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2011/06/27/abc-announces-fall-series-premiere-dates-late-starts-for-once-upon-a-time-man-up/96596/|date=June 27, 2011|work=TV by the Numbers|access-date=June 27, 2011}}</ref>\n\nOn November 3, 2011, the series was picked up for a full season of twenty-two episodes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2011/11/03/abc-picks-up-full-seasons-of-once-upon-a-time-last-man-standing-and-happy-endings-orders-additional-scripts-for-pan-am/109596|title=ABC Picks Up Full Seasons of 'Once Upon a Time,' 'Last Man Standing' and 'Happy Endings'|last=Seidman|first=Robert|work=TV by the Numbers|date=November 3, 2011|access-date=November 4, 2011}}</ref> On January 12, 2012, the order was increased to twenty-four episodes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2012/01/12/abc-orders-more-of-last-man-standing/|title=Last Man Standing extended by two more weeks on ABC|last=Rice|first=Lynette|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=January 12, 2012|accessdate=October 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn May 11, 2012, ABC renewed the series for a second season set to air in the [[2012\u201313 United States network television schedule|2012\u20132013 season]] in November.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/05/11/private-practice-body-of-proof-renewed-by-abc-scandal-gcb-canceled/133753|title=Updated: Private Practice, 'Body of Proof' Renewed; 'Last Man Standing,' 'Scandal' & 'Apt 23\u2032 Renewed Too; 'GCB' Canceled|work=Tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com|accessdate=May 12, 2012|date=May 12, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvline.com/2012/07/26/fall-tv-abc-announces-premiere-dates|title=Fall TV: ABC Announces Premiere Dates|last=Mitovich|first=Matt|work=TV Line|date=July 26, 2012|access-date=July 26, 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn June 11, 2012, [[Tim Doyle]] was hired as the new showrunner of the series. Doyle was the third showrunner that the series had had since it entered production. Doyle replaced Kevin Abbott, who joined the staff as the showrunner mid-way in the first season. Abbott replaced series creator Jack Burditt, who was the showrunner for the first thirteen episodes. Unlike Burditt, who is no longer credited as an executive producer, Abbott continued to serve as an executive producer while showrunning the fellow ABC sitcom ''[[Malibu Country]]'' starring [[Reba McEntire]]. Both ''Last Man Standing'' and ''Malibu Country'' aired as a part of ABC's Friday night lineup for the 2012\u20132013 primetime television season.<ref>{{cite web|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|url=https://www.deadline.com/2012/06/tim-doyle-joins-abcs-last-man-standing-as-new-showrunner|title=Tim Doyle Joins ABC's 'Last Man Standing' As New Showrunner|website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=August 11, 2012|date=June 11, 2012}}</ref> On November 8, 2012, Abbott re-joined the ''Last Man Standing'' crew full-time, after a stint in rehab, and gave Nastaran Dibai full showrunning duties of ''Malibu Country''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |url=https://www.deadline.com/2012/11/nastaran-dibai-to-run-maliby-country-kevin-abbott-rejoins-last-man-standing/ |title=Nastaran Dibai To Run 'Malibu Country', Kevin Abbott Rejoins 'Last Man Standing' |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=January 28, 2012 |access-date=November 10, 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn June 11, 2012, it was announced that [[Alexandra Krosney]] (Kristin) was let go from the show for creative reasons.<ref>{{cite news|author=Michael Ausiello|url=http://tvline.com/2012/06/11/last-man-standing-alexandra-krosney-leaving|title=Last Man Standing Drops Alexandra Krosney \u2013 Season 2|work=TVLine|accessdate=June 12, 2012}}</ref> Krosney was replaced by [[Amanda Fuller]] in season 2.<ref>{{cite web|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|url=https://www.deadline.com/2012/08/shiri-appleby-poised-to-recur-on-nbcs-chicago-fire-more-tv-castings|title=TV Castings \u2013 Chicago Fire, Last Man Standing, Arrow|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=June 27, 2012|access-date=August 10, 2012}}</ref> On June 19, 2012, it was also announced that twins Luke and Evan Kruntchev, who played the role of Boyd in season 1, would not be returning; they were replaced by Flynn Morrison in season 2.<ref name=\"Season2Recast\">{{cite web|last=Baldwin|first=Kristen|url=https://ew.com/article/2012/08/10/last-man-standing-tim-allen-abc/|title='Last Man Standing' adds actors to play Tim Allen's daughter, grandson|work=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=August 10, 2012}}</ref> The character of Boyd was also [[Soap opera rapid aging syndrome|age-advanced]] from two years old to five years old.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2012/06/last-man-standing-season-2-retools-family-dynamic-and-ages-up-the-kid.html|title='Last Man Standing' Season 2 retools family dynamic and ages up the kid|work=From Inside the Box|accessdate=June 22, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120622183933/http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2012/06/last-man-standing-season-2-retools-family-dynamic-and-ages-up-the-kid.html|archivedate=June 22, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[Jordan Masterson]] plays Ryan, Boyd's father, in a recurring role beginning in season 2.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/News/Kecks-Exclusives-Last-Man-Standing-1052001.aspx|title=Keck's Exclusives: Last Man Standing Recasts Role \u2013 Today's News: Our Take|work=TVGuide.com|date=August 16, 2012|access-date=October 19, 2012}}</ref> The role was previously played by [[Nick Jonas]], who guest-starred in one episode in season 1.<ref name=\"Season2Recast\"/>\n\nThe second season initially received a 13-episode order. ABC announced on November 12, 2012, that an additional three scripts had been ordered.<ref>Andreeva, Nellie. \"ABC Comedies 'Malibu Country' & 'Last Man Standing' Get Orders For More Scripts\". deadline.com on November 12, 2012. [https://www.deadline.com/2012/11/abc-comedies-malibu-country-last-man-standing-get-orders-for-additional-scripts/]</ref> On November 27, five more episodes were ordered to bring the second-season episode total to 18.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/11/28/last-man-standing-and-malibu-country-get-5-more-episodes/159564/|title='Last Man Standing' and 'Malibu Country' Get 5 More Episodes Each|last=Seidman|first=Robert|work=TV By the Numbers|date=November 28, 2012|access-date=November 29, 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn May 10, 2013, the series was renewed for a third season,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/05/10/last-man-standing-renewed_n_3103778.html |title='Last Man Standing' Renewed: ABC Orders Season 3 |publisher=Huffingtonpost.com |date= May 10, 2013|access-date=May 15, 2013 |first=Chris |last=Harnick}}</ref> which premiered on September 20, 2013, and ended on April 25, 2014, after 22 episodes.<ref name=\"ABC Fall 2013 Premiere Dates\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/07/16/abc-sets-premiere-dates-for-2013-2014-season-including-s-h-i-e-l-d-once-upon-a-time-in-wonderland-modern-family-scandal-more/192284 |title=ABC Sets Premiere Dates for 2013\u20132014 Including 'Marvel's Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.', 'Once Upon A Time In Wonderland' & More |last=Kondolojy |first=Amanda |work=TV by the Numbers |date=July 16, 2013 |access-date=July 16, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130719052314/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/07/16/abc-sets-premiere-dates-for-2013-2014-season-including-s-h-i-e-l-d-once-upon-a-time-in-wonderland-modern-family-scandal-more/192284/ |archivedate=July 19, 2013 }}</ref>\n\nOn May 10, 2014, ABC renewed ''Last Man Standing'' for a fourth season, which premiered on October 3, 2014.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://ew.com/article/2014/05/10/last-man-standing-renewed-for-4th-season/|title='Last Man Standing' renewed for 4th season |website=Entertainment Weekly |date=May 10, 2014 |accessdate=October 1, 2019}}</ref> Allen and Elizondo guest-starred as their ''Last Man Standing'' characters in a crossover episode with the fellow ABC Friday sitcom ''[[Cristela]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.etonline.com/tv/159432_tim_allen_guest_stars_on_cristela/|title=Tim Allen Guest Stars on 'Cristela' in 'Last Man Standing' Crossover Episode!|work=Entertainment Tonight|date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nOn May 10, 2015, ABC announced the show had been renewed for a fifth season. ''Last Man Standing'' had become a solid performer for the Friday night lineup at ABC, which with the help of ''[[Shark Tank]]'' and ''[[20/20 (American TV program)|20/20]]'' has become the top network among adults 18\u201349 for the night. Leading off Friday night for ABC, the sitcom averaged a 1.8 rating in adults 18\u201349 and 8.2 million viewers overall, according to Nielsen's Live+7 estimates.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2015/05/10/last-man-standing-renewed-5th-season|title=Last Man Standing renewed for season 5|work=Entertainment Weekly}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/last-man-standing-renewed-season-5-abc-1201491995/|title='Last Man Standing' Renewed: Season 5 Greenlit by ABC \u2013 Variety|author=Elizabeth Wagmeister|work=Variety|date=2015|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nOn May 13, 2016, ABC renewed the series for a sixth season, which premiered on September 23, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://release-date.info/tv-series/last-man-standing-season-6-release-date-580039271/ |publisher=TV Series |title='Last Man Standing' Season 6 Premiere Date Revealed |date=June 30, 2016 |access-date=August 26, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160831185053/http://release-date.info/tv-series/last-man-standing-season-6-release-date-580039271/ |archive-date=August 31, 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nOn March 15, 2020, production on the series was shut down during the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/last-man-standing-the-orville-shut-down-over-production-coronavirus-1202883985/ |title='Last Man Standing' & 'The Orville' Join List Of Shows Shut Down Over Coronavirus |website=Deadline |date=March 15, 2020 |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |access-date=March 16, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n===Cancellation===\nOn May 10, 2017, ABC canceled ''Last Man Standing'' after six seasons, despite the series being the second-most-watched ABC sitcom during the 2016\u201317 season (based on Live+7 figures), with ratings remaining mostly steady during its sixth season.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://deadline.com/2017/05/last-man-standing-canceled-by-abc-after-6-seasons-1202089263/|title='Last Man Standing' Canceled By ABC After 6 Seasons|date=May 10, 2017|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=May 10, 2017}}</ref> A representative for 20th Century Fox Television said cancellation decisions are made by ABC.&nbsp;\"This was a scheduling decision,\" wrote Jori Arancio, senior vice president of ABC Entertainment and ABC Studios. ABC and its production partner for the show, 20th Century Fox Television, typically negotiate licensing fees prior to each season; however, the network decided to cancel the show without doing so. Also, the contract between 20th Century Fox Television and ABC for the show, in which 20th Century Fox Television covered the cost of production, had expired after six seasons. Had the series been renewed for a seventh season, ABC would have been required to pick up ''Last Man Standing''{{'}}s production costs, which the network was unwilling to do.<ref name=nolte_cancellation>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailywire.com/news/16317/despite-high-ratings-abc-cancels-trump-friendly-john-nolte|title=Despite High Ratings, ABC Cancels Trump-Friendly Sitcom 'Last Man Standing'|date=May 11, 2017|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nThe cancellation was met with outrage from the show's fans, many of whom took to [[social media]] to voice their displeasure and petition for another network to pick up the show.<ref name=Mooney>{{cite web|last1=Mooney|first1=Paula|title='LAST MAN STANDING' CANCELED WITH 8.1M VIEWERS: FANS BOYCOTT ABC OVER TIM ALLEN'S CONSERVATIVE CHRISTIAN ROLE|url=http://www.inquisitr.com/4212160/last-man-standing-canceled-with-8-1m-viewers-fans-boycott-abc-over-tim-allens-conservative-christian-role/|website=Inquisitir|accessdate=May 12, 2017}}</ref> It also happened some months after lead actor Tim Allen (who is also a real-life Republican) said in an interview on ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]'', that being a Republican in Hollywood is \"like 1930s Germany. You gotta be real careful around here, you know. You'll get beat up if you don't believe what everybody believes\". His comment was widely criticized, especially his comparing the treatment of Republicans in Hollywood with [[Nazi Germany]].<ref name=\"Maglio\">{{cite web|last1=Maglio|first1=Tony|last2=Gajewski|first2=Ryan|title=Did Tim Allen's Nazi Germany Joke Help Kill 'Last Man Standing'?|url=https://www.thewrap.com/last-man-standing-canceled-tim-allen-nazi-germany-joke/|website=TheWrap|accessdate=May 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\nA viewer petition on the website Change.org calling for ABC to reinstate ''Last Man Standing'' surpassed 380,000 signatures as of May 23, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://us.blastingnews.com/showbiz-tv/2017/05/last-man-standing-replacing-the-mick-on-fox-network-hears-from-ptc-001718683.html|title=Blasting News|last=|first=|date=May 23, 2017|website=|access-date=May 27, 2017}}</ref> In a conference call with reporters earlier in May, ABC president [[Channing Dungey]] stated, \"''Last Man Standing'' was a challenging one for me, because it was a steady performer. Once we made the decision not to continue with comedy on Friday, it was just kind of that's where we landed.\" Dungey cited studio ownership, future creative direction, ratings and viewer engagement as all factors in her decision.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tribunist.com/news/tim-allen-breaks-silence-on-cancellation-of-last-man-standing-as-petition-clears-140000-signatures/ |title=Tim Allen Breaks Silence on Cancellation of \"Last Man Standing\" as Petition Clears 140,000+ Signatures |website=Tribuist.com |date=May 16, 2017 |accessdate=May 17, 2017 }}{{Dead link|date=February 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> A year later, the petition's signatures had grown to 438,000.<ref name=ddln0511 />\n\nOn May 16, 2017 Tim Allen expressed his displeasure with the cancellation, writing: \"Stunned and blindsided by the network I called home for the last six years.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.aol.com/article/entertainment/2017/05/16/tim-allen-abc-tweet-last-man-standing-cancelled/22094047/|title=Tim Allen lashes out at ABC after 'Last Man Standing' cancellation|last=Staff|first=AOL|work=AOL.com|access-date=May 17, 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn May 20, 2017, Howard Kurtzman, president of [[20th Century Fox Television]], reportedly showed some interest in his studio continuing to produce the show. \"We're starting to explore that,\" Kurtzman said.  \"... Jonnie and I are hopeful that we can find another home for it.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aol.com/article/entertainment/2017/05/20/last-man-standing-20th-century-fox-tv-will-seek-new-home-for/22099687/|title=AOL.com|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=May 27, 2017}}</ref> ''Variety'' also confirmed in an exclusive report that 20th Century Fox Television would shop the series to other networks and streaming services in hopes it would be picked up for a seventh season;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/last-man-standing-new-home-tim-allen-1202434432/ |title='Last Man Standing': 20th Century Fox TV Will Seek New Home for Tim Allen Comedy |website=Variety.com |last=Holloway |first=Daniel| date=May 18, 2017 |accessdate=May 18, 2017}}</ref> another home was not quickly found, however.\n\nIn August 2017, Allen expressed his appreciation for support by the show's fans to bring it back, and said the talent behind the show had much more to add.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2018/03/29/roseanne-ratings-put-pressure-on-networks-to-revive-conservative-show-last-man-standing.html |title='Roseanne' ratings put pressure on networks to revive conservative show 'Last Man Standing' |publisher=Fox News |first=Sasha |last=Savitsky |date= March 29, 2018 |access-date=March 29, 2018 }}</ref>\n\n===Revival on Fox===\nOn May 3, 2018, Allen wrote that a return \"just might be a reality\" and prompted the show's supporters to \"keep it up\".<ref>{{cite news |title=Tim Allen teases 'Last Man Standing' return |date=May 3, 2018 |access-date=May 3, 2018 |publisher=Fox News |first=Sasha |last=Savitsky |url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2018/05/03/tim-allen-teases-last-man-standing-return.html }}</ref> The same day, TVLine reported that [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] was \"poised to\" resurrect ''Last Man Standing'' for the 2018\u201319 TV season, adding that Tim Allen is \"officially on board\".<ref>{{cite news |title=Last Man Standing Revival Eyed at Fox, Tim Allen Officially on Board |date=May 3, 2018 |access-date=May 5, 2018 |work=TVLine.com |first=Michael |last=Ausiello |url=http://tvline.com/2018/05/03/last-man-standing-revival-fox-season-7-tim-allen/ }}</ref> ''[[Deadline Hollywood]]'' reported that Fox was in talks for another season, but it was \"by no means a sure thing\", suggesting it would depend on whether the actors could be re-signed \"at reasonable salaries\".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/last-man-standing-eyes-return-fox-tim-allen-1202379904/ |title='Last Man Standing' Eyes Resurrection At Fox With Star Tim Allen Set to Return |newspaper=Deadline Hollywood |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |date=May 3, 2018 |access-date=May 8, 2018 }}</ref> On May 11, 2018, Fox TV's CEOs and chairmen announced that Fox had officially picked up ''Last Man Standing'' for a seventh season.<ref>{{cite magazine |url= http://people.com/tv/tim-allen-last-man-standing-returns-fox/ |title=Tim Allen's Last Man Standing Is Returning to TV 1 Year After Cancellation |magazine=People |date=May 11, 2018 |access-date=May 11, 2018 |first=Michele |last=Corriston }}</ref><ref name=returnconfirmed>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2018/05/11/tim-allens-last-man-standing-revived-fox/603136002/|date=May 11, 2018|title=Last Man Standing' resurfaces at Fox, a year after ABC canceled it|work=[[USA Today]]|last=Levin|first=Gary|accessdate=May 11, 2018}}</ref><ref name=ddln0511>{{Cite news|url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/last-man-fox-seventh-season-tim-allen-1202388669/|title='Last Man Standing' Resurrected At Fox For Season 7 With Original Cast Led By Tim Allen|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=May 11, 2018|website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=May 11, 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/la-fi-ct-fox-schedule-20180514-story.html|title=Tim Allen's 'Last Man Standing' returns \u2014 this time on Fox's fall schedule|last=Battaglio|first=Stephen|website=latimes.com|date=May 14, 2018|access-date=May 14, 2018}}</ref> Dana Walden, chairman of Fox Television Group, later hinted that the return of ''Last Man Standing'' was in part a response to the huge success of the ''[[Roseanne]]'' revival on ABC earlier in 2018: \"Obviously, I think everyone took a good, hard look at the performance of ''Roseanne''. It did so well, and it certainly did remind us that we have a huge, iconic comedy star in our Fox family in Tim Allen.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cheatsheet.com/entertainment/who-is-not-returning-last-man-standing-recast.html/?a=viewall|title=Who Isn't Returning for 'Last Man Standing' Season 7? Two Roles Are Being Recast|last=Morrow|first=Brendan|website=cheatsheet.com|date=July 3, 2018|access-date=July 12, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn July 2, Fox announced that, in addition to Allen, series regulars Nancy Travis, Amanda Fuller, Hector Elizondo, Christoph Sanders, Jordan Masterson and Jonathan Adams had all signed on to appear in the season 7 reboot. Molly Ephraim and Flynn Morrison both opted not to return for the new season,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2018/07/02/last-man-standing-molly-ephraim-season-7-mandy-recast/|title=Last Man Standing Shake-Up: 2 Major Roles Being Recast Ahead of Season 7 (EXCLUSIVE)|website=TVLine|first=Michael|last=Ausiello|date=July 2, 2018}}</ref> with Fox announcing their roles (\"Mandy\" and \"Boyd\", respectively) would be recast ahead of season 7.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/last-man-standing-molly-ephraim-flynn-morrison-1202863659/|title=Tim 'Last Man Standing' Regulars Molly Ephraim, Flynn Morrison Exit Ahead of Season 7, Roles to Be Recast |last=Otterson |first=Joe |publisher=variety.com |date=July 2, 2018 |access-date=July 3, 2018}}</ref> On August 6, 2018, it was announced that Molly McCook and [[Jet Jurgensmeyer]] would be taking over the roles of Mandy and Boyd, respectively. The article also stated that Kaitlyn Dever, who recently signed on to play a lead role in the 2019 [[Netflix]] miniseries ''[[Unbelievable (miniseries)|Unbelievable]]'', would return as \"Eve\" in a recurring role only.<ref name=recast>{{cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2018/08/06/last-man-standing-mandy-recast-molly-mccook-season-7-fox/ |title=Last Man Standing's Mandy Recast: Molly McCook Replaces Molly Ephraim |date=August 6, 2018 |first=Michael |last=Ausiello |website=TVLine |access-date=August 7, 2018 }}</ref>\n\nFor the seventh season, the show aired in the same Friday night time slot as for the last five of its six seasons on ABC; the show was renewed for an eighth season, and was moved to a new time slot, as Fox had signed an agreement to air ''[[WWE SmackDown]]'' on Friday nights beginning in fall 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/fox-wwe-close-five-year-deal-bring-smackdown-network-1123487|title=Fox and WWE Close Five-Year Deal to Bring 'SmackDown' to Network|last=Guthrie|first=Marisa|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=June 27, 2018|accessdate=June 27, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.si.com/extra-mustard/2018/06/27/wwe-fox-smackdown-live-usa-monday-night-raw-five-year-deal|title=Cord cutting, millennials can't stop Vince McMahon and WWE|last=Traina|first=Jimmy|work=Sports Illustrated|date=June 27, 2018|accessdate=June 27, 2018}}</ref> When the Fox schedule was released in May 2019, ''Last Man Standing'' was placed in a Thursday night time slot, but only in weeks when Fox does not air [[Thursday Night Football|NFL]] or [[XFL (2020)|XFL]] games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/fox-fall-2019-20-schedule-upfronts-new-shows-empire-the-masked-singer-the-orville-last-man-standing-1202613344/|title=Fox Fall 2019-20 Schedule: WWE, NFL, No Live-Action Comedies With 'Last Man Standing' Held, 'Empire' & 'Resident' To Tuesday|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|work=Deadline.com|date=May 13, 2019|accessdate=May 14, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/10/xfl-schedule-2020-abc-fox-espn-fs1-1202765955/|title=XFL Schedule: ABC, Fox & Their Cable Outlets Set 10-Week Regular Season Dates Plus Playoffs|first=Erik|last=Pedersen|work=Deadline.com|date=October 22, 2019|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref> On October 24, 2019, it was announced that season eight has been scheduled to premiere on January 2, 2020, with 2 back-to-back episodes airing in an hour timeslot for three weeks on January 2, 9 and 16, before returning to a one-episode-a-week timeslot of 8/7c starting on January 23.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/10/fox-midseason-premiere-dates-last-man-standing-duncanville-deputy-masked-singer-outmatched-9-1-1-lone-star-1202768301/|title=Fox Midseason Premiere Dates: 'Last Man Standing', 'Flirty Dancing', 'Deputy', 'Duncanville' & More|last=Pedersen|first=Nellie Andreeva,Erik|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|date=2019-10-24|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-10-25|last3=Pedersen|first3=Erik}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\n[[File:Last Man Standing Cast - Men.png|thumb|right|(L to R) ''Last Man Standing'' stars [[H\u00e9ctor Elizondo]], [[Tim Allen]] and [[Christoph Sanders]]]]\n\nOn review aggregation website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], season one holds an approval rating of 14% based on 37 reviews, while the average rating is 4.14/10. The site's critical consensus reads, \"''Last Man Standing'' is a thoroughly middling sitcom relying on jokes that feel alternately dated or hostile.\"<ref name=\"Rotten Tomatoes S1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/last-man-standing/s01/|title=Last Man Standing: Season 1|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|access-date=May 27, 2017}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the season has a weighted average score of 33 out of 100, based on 24 critics, indicating \"generally unfavorable reviews\".<ref name=\"Metacritic S1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/last-man-standing-2011|title=Last Man Standing (2011) \u2013 Season 1 Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111010215616/http://www.metacritic.com/tv/last-man-standing-2011|archive-date=October 10, 2011|url-status=live|accessdate=May 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\n''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' called the series \"a predictable sitcom with a stupid premise and bad acting\".<ref name=\"HR 2011-10-05\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/last-man-standing-tv-review-244660|title=Last Man Standing: TV Review|last=Goodman|first=Tim|date=October 5, 2011|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|access-date=March 27, 2015}}</ref> ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'': \"The jokes and plots have been efficiently constructed, but most have no traction; they slide right off you, and the characters themselves seem disconnected from one another.\"<ref name=\"LA Times 2011-10-11\">{{cite news|url=https://articles.latimes.com/2011/oct/11/entertainment/la-et-last-man-standing-20111011|title=Last Man Standing': Review|last=Lloyd|first=Robert|date=October 11, 2011|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|access-date=March 27, 2015}}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' offered a slightly more favorable review of the show: \"When I look at the now-rounded softness of Tim Allen, and note once again how his sandpaper voice contrasts winningly with his hopeful eyes, it's impossible to plunge a shiv into this series.\"<ref name=\"EW 2011-10-11\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2011/10/11/last-man-standing-tim-allen-home-improvement|title='Last Man Standing': Tim Allen returns to TV, no 'Home Improvement'|last=Tucker|first=Ken|author-link=Ken Tucker|date=October 11, 2011|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|access-date=March 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\nSeason two of the series holds an approval rating of 40% on Rotten Tomatoes.<ref name=\"Rotten Tomatoes S2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/last-man-standing/s02/|title=Last Man Standing: Season 2|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|access-date=March 27, 2015}}</ref> \n\nSeason seven holds an approval rating of 58% based on 12 reviews and an average rating of 5.34/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"''Last Man Standing'' isn't the most realistic sitcom on the dial, but its idealistic representation of opposites living in harmony offers sorely needed hope during divided times.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/last_man_standing/s07|title=Last Man Standing: Season 7 (2018)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=October 28, 2018}}</ref> On Metacritic, the season has a weighted average score of 58 out of 100, based on 6 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/last-man-standing-2011/season-7|title=Last Man Standing (2011) \u2013 Season 7 Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=September 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\n''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' commented: \"I think it's time the folks involved with ''Last'' take a closer look at ''[[All in the Family]]'', in which the prejudice was built around real jokes.\"<ref name=\"EW 2012-11-02\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2012/11/02/malibu-country-last-man-standing-mitt-romney-reba-mcentire-tim-allen|title='Last Man Standing' and 'Malibu Country': Season premiere reviews|last=Tucker|first=Ken|author-link=Ken Tucker|date=November 2, 2012|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|access-date=March 27, 2015}}</ref> ''[[The A.V. Club]]'': \"The problem with ''Last Man Standing''{{'}}s attempts to go political is exemplified by the first scene of the season premi\u00e8re, which remains one of the most uncomfortable scenes of television I've ever watched ... doing its best to push buttons in the audience that don't need to be pushed, as if it thinks what made [[Norman Lear|[Norman] Lear]]'s sitcoms a success was the yelling or the mentions of social issues that people sometimes argued about.\"<ref name=\"AV Club 2013-04-01\">{{cite news|url=https://www.avclub.com/article/ilast-man-standingis-second-season-was-the-weirdes-95857|title=Last Man Standing's second season was the weirdest sitcom season since 'Til Death|last=VanDerWerff|first=Emily|date=April 1, 2013|newspaper=[[The A.V. Club]]|access-date=October 6, 2019}}</ref> [[Philadelphia Media Network|Philly.com]] wrote about season three: \"The unlikely comeback vehicle for Tim Allen, ''Last Man Standing'' on ABC, is a thoroughly traditional, absolutely charming sitcom. [...] ''Last Man'' is both economical and efficient, getting excellent comic mileage out of the most marginal bit players.\"<ref name=\"Philly.com 2013-12-20\">{{cite web|url=http://www.philly.com/philly/columnists/david_hiltbrand/20131221_Lots_of_funny_business_all_over_TV.html|title=Lots of funny business all over TV|last=Hiltbrand|first=David|date=December 20, 2013|publisher=[[Philadelphia Media Network|Philly.com]]|access-date=March 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe series is particularly popular among [[American conservatism|conservatives]], many of whom view the show as a counterpoint to ''[[Modern Family]]'', another 20th Century Fox sitcom that airs on ABC and features more [[Modern liberalism in the United States|liberal]] ideologies.<ref name=nolte_cancellation/> A study conducted during the [[2016 United States presidential election|2016 U.S. presidential election]] found that it was the tenth most popular show on television with Republicans.<ref name=\"Business Insider\">{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/favorite-tv-shows-of-democrats-and-republicans-2016-7/#10-last-man-standing-abc-11|title=The 10 favorite TV shows of Democrats and Republicans|website=[[Business Insider]]|access-date=May 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\nABC's series premiere of ''Last Man Standing'' drew a 3.5 adults 18\u201349 rating. That was 9% better than the 3.2 adults 18\u201349 rating for the series premiere of ''[[No Ordinary Family]]'' in the same time-slot the previous year (which was two weeks earlier in the season). Season 2 of ''Last Man Standing'' premiered with a 2.0, down about 38% from its first-season premiere, but up about 18% from the previous season's finale.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/11/05/friday-final-tv-ratings-last-man-standing-and-malibu-country-adjusted-up-fringe-and-nikita-adjusted-down/156158/ |title=Friday Final TV Ratings: 'Last Man Standing' and 'Malibu Country' Adjusted Up; 'Fringe' and 'Nikita' Adjusted Down |last=Kondology |first=Amanda |publisher=[[TV By the Numbers]] |date=November 5, 2012|accessdate=December 8, 2012}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Season\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Timeslot ([[Eastern Time Zone (North America)|ET]])\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Network\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | No. of<br />episodes\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"3\" | Premiered\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"3\" | Ended\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | TV season\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Rank\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Viewers<br />(million)\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Live + DVR<br />viewers\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Premiere viewers<br />(million)\n! scope=\"col\" | Premiere 18\u201349<br />rating/share\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Finale viewers<br />(million)\n! scope=\"col\" | Finale 18\u201349<br />rating/share\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 1\n| Tuesday 8:00{{nbsp}}pm\n| rowspan=\"6\" | [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n| 24\n| October 11, 2011\n| 12.93<ref name=1x01>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2011/10/12/tuesday-final-ratings-last-man-ncis-90210-dancing-adjusted-up-ringer-body-of-proof-adjusted-down/106994|title=Tuesday Final Ratings: 'Last Man,' 'NCIS,' '90210,' 'Dancing' Adjusted Up; 'Ringer,' 'Body Of Proof' Adjusted Down \u2013 Ratings |publisher=[[TV By the Numbers]] |accessdate=May 3, 2012}}</ref>\n| 3.4/10<ref name=1x01/>\n| May 8, 2012\n| 6.62<ref name=season1finaleratings>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/05/09/tuesday-final-ratings-