-2-2020/|title='Last Man Standing' and 'Deputy' adjust up: Thursday final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|date=January 7, 2020|accessdate=January 18, 2020}}</ref>\n| 1.0/5<ref name=\"8.01\"/>\n| {{n/a|TBA}}\n| {{n/a|TBA}}\n| {{n/a|TBA}}\n| [[2019-20 United States network television schedule|2019\u201320]]\n| {{n/a|TBA}}\n| {{n/a|TBA}}\n| {{n/a|TBA}}\n|}\n\n===Awards and nominations===\n''Last Man Standing'' was nominated for a 2012 [[People's Choice Award]] for \"Favorite New TV Comedy\", but lost to [[CBS]]'s ''[[2 Broke Girls]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Association\n! Category\n! Nominee / episode\n! Outcome\n|-\n|2011\n|ASCAP Film and Television Music Awards\n|Top Television Series{{citation needed|date=November 2015}}\n|Carl Thiel (composer)\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2012\n|[[People's Choice Awards]]\n|[[38th People's Choice Awards#Television|Favorite New TV Comedy]]\n|''Last Man Standing''\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[Kids' Choice Awards]]\n|[[2012 Kids' Choice Awards#Favorite TV Actor|Favorite TV Actor]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Tim Allen\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[TV Guide]] Magazine's Fan Favorites Awards\n|Favorite Comeback<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/tv-guide-magazine-1045829/|title=TV Guide Magazine Fan Favorites Awards Winners Revealed!|publisher=CBS Interactive Inc.|accessdate=January 19, 2017}}</ref>\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[Young Artist Awards]]\n|[[33rd Young Artist Awards#Best Performance in a TV Series - Supporting Young Actress|Best Performance in a TV Series (Comedy or Drama) \u2013 Supporting Young Actress]]\n|[[Kaitlyn Dever]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2013\n|[[Environmental Media Awards]]\n|Television Episodic Comedy<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.green4ema.org/ema-awards/ema-awards-past-recipients-and-honorees/|title=EMA Awards Past and present|publisher=The Environmental Media Association|accessdate=January 19, 2017}}</ref>\n|\"Mother Fracker\"\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|ASCAP Film and Television Music Awards\